entries.femaleVariant: All right, I'm in position. Preparing our evac route now.
And Aymeric, this should go without sayin', but... stay in character.
And Aurore, this should go without sayin', but... stay in character.
What I wouldn't give for a Broseph and a burger…
Shh! Hansen's got guests, man…!
Copy that. I'll check it out.
A pleasure to see you both.
Let's keep movin'.
Changing the subject… did you enjoy yourselves at the Black Sapphire?
A Porsche 911.
A Quadra Turbo-R.
Perhaps you know this man, Greyson…? He wanted to sell me a classic Porsche once owned by a famous American rockerboy.
I was shopping for a Quadra Turbo-R, a model from fifty-five.
Ah, a connoisseur of the classics.
I collect many cars.
Your source is wrong.
Which gives us a chance to chat.
I have a diverse collection. I work much and spend even more – you understand.
Of course. Although my spending differs from yours.
Then your man misled you. Perhaps by accident, perhaps not.
Please, I have vodka. Help yourselves.
I'm sure you never put pleasure before business, but I insist. A symbolic drink.
Haha, I could not say it better myself. Symbolic, yes.
[Don't take a drink] You have many friends.
[Don't take a drink] The Americans don't really like you.
You have many friends, it seems.
Your old friends in the New States – there is bad blood, no?
[Hand drink to Alex] You take it.
[Take a drink] Cheers.
None for me. All yours, Aurore.
I never say no to good vodka.
To your health.
[Hand drink to Alex] You take it.
Ah, right, I'd almost forgotten. My friends in La Santé send their regards. C Block.
Are you sure? You spent two years in that prison. Under a false name.
That's right. In the VIP wing. But the cockroaches in C Block don't know who is there.
Let's begin.
Follow me.
A pleasure to see you both.
This way.
So tell me – how do ya like NC now that you're back?
This hollow shell? With shining promises and colorful pleasures without meaning?
Kinda like suckin' your own cock, huh? Pardon the analogy. but you're right, I agree.
We were in different blocks.
Ah, the tattoo I remember.
Pff, this Raquel is clearly mistaken. Max security is separate from the VIP wing, where I stayed. Heh, thank God.
Ah, yes, the rat tattoo! I remember! Oh, please give Raquel my warmest regards.
Wait, did I say Raquel? I meant Ruth. From B Block, not C.
Then give my regards to Ruth as well.
We were both mistaken.
Which gives us a chance to chat.
Heh! Then say hello to Ruth.
So... we were both mistaken.
How many years have you been in Night City? They say you served with Militech once.
Seven years now. And yes, before that it was my mission to plant an NUS flag on this soil.
Ah, the tailor of Kerry Eurodyne. Oh, he is so flavorful! Mmm, I must have a taste, hahaha!
We spoke of, uh, Lizzy Wizzy's stylist. Oh, magnifique!
Are you certain? If that's the case, I could've asked her then and there. She was at the party, too.
I'm afraid I don't remember.
I'm afraid I don't remember.
Never mind.
Uh, so many in Night City ooze style – ah, I just don't know. Lizzy Wizzy, Kerry Eurodyne, Arif Iqbal – I spoke of each, no? Perhaps I am wrong?
Perfect!
Ah, it's a small problem. It is time to attend to business, no?
Your sister certainly is the more talkative of you two.
You noticed?
I'm sorry, Colonel, but you are teasing the wrong cock.
Hah! Anyone with even a bit of cred in France knows who they are.
We can put you in contact, easily enough.
There is one "but".
There is one "but".
We are well acquainted.
Oui, one fat, juicy "but." They have, uh, sentenced me to death.
For that much cash, I can ask. But no assurance, that would cost more.
Yes, I and Le Collectif, we are very close.
Let's begin.
Follow me.
Ugh, my brother, he talks little.
Sometime, I find this creepy. But not you I hope?
Hey, just met the guy.
Good, you made it.
Have you been with Hansen since the beginning?
Since the op in Night City,  you mean?
Could say that. But we served together earlier, too.
Got our people mannin' the whole stadium. Drone-aided scans providin' surveillance support, too.
Good, you made it.
Need you to leave your weapons here.
Good luck.
We can begin. The mainframe is ready.
We can begin. The mainframe is ready.
Is Hansen here?
Quite the stadium.
So... this is your celebrated stadium.
The colonel is here already?
Lead the way.
You look nervous.
Murphy… It seems familiar. No, I believe we have met.
Oh, let's finish this quickly. My hangover is killing me.
Area's off limits. Move along.
[Leave weapons]
[Leave weapons]
A Rayfield Aerondight.
I had my eyes on a Rayfield Aerondight. Second-hand, of course. The new ones are overpriced.
Interesting. Because the first I ever heard of you, why, it was about you being  in the market for a used car. But certainly not a Rayfield.
Ah, a fact about me that is not so easy to learn.
Very true.
I do not know any Raquel.
Symbolic…
Mhmmm.
[Take a drink] Symbolically.
Lizzy Wizzy's stylist.
Kerry Eurodyne's tailor.
Arif Iqbal's personal couturier.
Uh, the couturier of, uh, Arif Iqbal – oh, that tasty morsel on WNS News.
You sure of this? I think I'd remember if that son-of-a-bitch's name came up…
We can manage that.
It will cost more.
Impossible.
It will cost. More than your two stacks. Much more.
Call it four, then.
You should expect to have eyes on you all day today. Kurt got a tip – the FIA plans to pull some gonk move.
You should expect to have eyes on you all day today. Kurt got a tip – the FIA plans to pull some gonk move.
This here's the heart of our little empire.
Hell, it's not even that little anymore.
Tell me – what do you do here, your operation, precisely?
Ah, how you sell these war machines – it's like a car salesman?
Now, here's somethin' that oughta pique your interest.
Remember Tijuana's pacification? Peruvian Revolution? Then you know what this baby can do.
This here's the latest 2078 model. Not slated to be revealed for a couple more months.
Improved AI support, reactive armor, additional cup holders – next-gen warfare, folks.
Also comes in candy apple red for a little extra.
Take your time. I'll need ten more minutes at least.
I couldn't get started  ealier without risk of bein' compromised.
Everyone knows Greyson. And this rock star. Yeah, I remember hearin' about this sale.
Well, it fell apart. Greyson was a fool – he weaseled out in the final hour.
True. War is an expensive hobby.
Huh. Not the kind to make reckless mistakes, that one…
Oh, I've visited many places, forged my fair share of stories, to be sure. Siberia was just one pitstop of many.
It's easier to count the places I haven't been. I know where to find what no one else has, and who to call to get it.
Murphy, we have foxes in the henhouse.
Are you sure?
Completely.
Uh, your friends are mistaken, I think.
I never worked for Petrochem.
I remember buying my way out.
I don't remember.
All change in the corporate world is effected with money. I could afford it.
A convenient answer. Generic, uninspired and almost definitely untrue.
No, I'm afraid this is not true. I never worked for Petrochem.
Oh, but you did. Maybe you've just forgotten?
Hm. If you do not like it, why make it your home?
I like eds. And NC's harvest of them is ripe as hell.
Ah... It must've been someone like you. Very much like you.
What are the odds?
You make it sound like you knew everyone in the joint.
Raquel, Ruth, there is no difference. I know none of them. I am just polite.
I was in the VIP wing. B and C Block have no access there.
Hahaha, yes, yes, that's the one. The fashion world isn't exactly my forte, so I'll need maybe a week to arrange it.
Eurodyne – it was his tailor. I'll be happy to arrange something.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Ma chère amie" b="" a=", it's been business all along."/>
Le Collectif and we, um... have a history, like you and your NUSA. We do not, er… make love. No fucking love at all.
Yet you're willing to risk this?
Pff, mere rumors, Colonel.
Songbird needs a moment to disarm the device.
Songbird needs a moment to disarm the device.
We haven't met yet. Name's Murphy.
We haven't met yet. Name's Murphy.
He is. Waitin' for you.
Fantastic.
I'm certain we haven't.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Oui, oui" b="" a=", you love to frequent the bordellos of Paris, no?"/>
I-- Uh– What?
Hahaha, I'm only fucking with you, Murphy. It is a pleasure.
Situation's under control. He ordered everyone checked out, though. No exceptions.
Huh... is that so?
That's right. Once an EBM and Petrochem monument to bloodsport, today a hub for global trade.
How very American.
Need you to leave your weapons here.
Huh, noticed and noted.
My, my, a diplomat...
Got our people mannin' the whole stadium. Drone-aided scans providin' surveillance support, too.
Many wish your colonel dead. He must be vigilant.
The situation's under control, though. He ordered everyone checked out. No exceptions.
What's your operation here, exactly?
Arms tradin', mostly. Need to start a war? End one? Plannin' a coup, maybe? We don't ask these questions.
Some. But our reach stretches 'round the globe. Japan, Australia, the Balkans, Lagos, you name it.
And this all is from Night City?
Kinda, heh, yeah. But wholesale only.
Suppose you're a dictator from some rinky-dink country. I dunno… Australia, let's say.
Tanks, choppers, subs – you want it, we got it. No red tape.
You have submarines?
Fresh out. But we sure did.
The FIA  knows about our meeting? They are interested?
We are not in a hurry.
Your man mentioned trouble. That NUS intelligence is interested in our meeting today.
I do not mind waiting.
The FIA knows about our meeting?
Murphy told us some shit hit the fan. That boogeymen know of us here, of our meeting.
Ugh, please, there is no need to hurry... We have a terrible hangover.
We are not in a hurry.
Heh. Both of you?
A bit of rhetoric. Aymeric doesn't drink. But when I do, both of us suffer.
Well, we'll fix that right quick... Do you often conduct business hungover?
[Move closer] Always.
[Move closer and touch] This is my first time.
[Move closer] It was an accident.
My first time, I give you my word.
Always. When your body believes it is dying, it does everything to survive. To be hungover is to be vigilant.
Ah well, it, uh, was an accident.
Murphy exaggerates. And he spoke out of turn.
We have only suspicions. I assure you, caution is our creed.
Oh, Colonel Kurt, you are too tense. I exaggerate. I wished only to see your reaction.
Huh. A unique philosophy… One I never heard.
Clever, no? It seems your clientele are painfully mundane, then.
I'm sure it is.
Pff, I know you don't believe me.
But I do.
Truly? Yet even I do not believe me.
You got blackout blitzed by accident? How?
A sad but common fate for a lover of vodka.
Now that I understand.
[Move closer] Of course I am.
Hah... Are you testing me?
[Move closer and touch] Not testing – teasing.
You check us out, we check you out... Kurt, it is the dance, it is the game! Loosen up!
No-no-no, we checked you before. Now I just tease.
This means I like you, no?
Hah! Fuck, you're entertaining.
Well, someone's trying to play us. Question is who.
Not your FIA, I 'ope.
Oh, actually, before I forget – I learned recently that we have a mutual friend.
A mutual friend?
My, you must have an impressive set of contacts, Colonel.
No. No, this is not something I wish to revisit. Not with someone I hardly know.
It's not a topic I like to discuss.
Raquel. Asked me to say hello. She did her time under max security, C Block, said her rat tattoo might jog your memory.
Ah, a fact about me not so easy to learn.
So true.
I went by a different name.
Also true.
A name wiped from all databases.
Well... not all, obviously.
"Trouble" is an exaggeration. Many people try to stick their noses into my business. I know this, and so I'm careful.
Were I you, I would say no different.
Hm-hm. I'm sure. I hear you're not the type to do anything hastily.
Ahem... Think I'm lying?
Of course.
Of course you are.
It makes no difference.
It does not matter.
I said nothing of the sort.
I said no such thing.
Then I'm fucking happy to know I misheard.
The value of my word, my honor, don't matter to you?
You are a criminal. As we are. This is business, not, uh... dinner with my grandmother.
Hah! We'll get along just fine.
Excuse me?
The only question that matters is whether your lie brings any harm. If our arrangement is truly safe, why should I care?
I assure you it is. Y'know, I find your pragmatism refreshing.
I was there under a false name.
Also true.
Alas, I did not know any Raquel, please excuse me.
And just who is this "friend" who remembers me so well?
But she very much insisted. Old thieves' code and all that.
Indeed.
Then it appears to be a great success. The things you have achieved here, impressive…
The FIA is still interested in you.
Why did you change sides?
It seems your old friends are still interested in you. That is why the FIA sniff around.
Why did you switch sides?
Call it a... sentimental attachment. The battle for NUSA's future drives us both.
I win my battles.
Because I don't need a convenient ideology to hide my business behind. I tossed the flag, but the suits in D.C. still remember me.
President Myers too?
She called just six months ago, in fact. Asked me to help with a mess she couldn't clean up herself. Bureaucracy, red tape and all that.
Interesting... And, uh, she calls still?
Not lately. Her administration recently encountered some, uh… turbulence along its path.
Interesting. Then are you different?
Ah, by the way... at the Sapphire, you asked me to contact a ceratain fashion type... Remind me who?
Murphy, we have a Code Three Thirteen. Foxes in the henhouse.
A tempting offer.
You know, Kurt... The arms trade – we keep our fingers out of this cookie jar.
Ooh, I have butterflies. A lucrative opportunity?
[Inspect Hansen's pistol] The arms trade is not for us.
Mhm, but I shouldn't sugarcoat it – I'm asking for a lot of hard work.
I see, but all I need's a nudge in the right direction. Some introductions, a little intelligence, one-time request, say… two hundred thousand?
Mmmm. Now I have butterflies.
Am I? But you're famous in Paris. You must have a connection.
Hmm... Sounds fair, good enough.
Rumors can be very dangerous. Especially when investigated, pursued, even turned inside out for truth.
Murphy! We have uninvited guests.
Just like you and the NUSA.
To work, then.
Shall we?
I see. Then he must trust you very much.
I heard the same about you.
How amusing. What else you must think of me, I wonder. What you must believe.
Then we have much in common, Colonel. I have heard the same about you.
Let me guess what else you have heard.
I do not waste time and energy on insignificant matters.
I conserve energy.
Hm. Interesting. I usually hear the exact opposite about myself.
So many fear criminals for their weapons, muscles, chrome… but are blind to the mind underneath.
A betrayed man, patient for his vengeance – he is dangerous.
So I heard. Is that why strip yourself of your memories and store them in external databanks?
In my quest for… mental hygiene, for spiritual economy. Do you believe in God, Colonel Hansen?
Hmm, which one? The eurodollar? The geopolitical powers that be? Or the Christian god? No, wastes of my time, all.
I see. Then I am curious how you will fare after this life has ended.
The cliché of a netrunner-ascetic? A techno-modified monk who treats his body as a temple?
What can I say? Guilty as charged.
You think I train the kung fu, that I know the secret of the vibrating fist.
Be careful, Colonel… perhaps I do.
The stadium is impressive.
Why did you stay in Night City? You are not from here.
Your operation in the stadium is most impressive. Perhaps even more than the ball at the Sapphire.
Say… it's been a while since you were last in Night City, hasn't it? Not since Cynosure.
You are not from here.
One can't work without the other. To make billions from the arms trade, you have to first line the pockets of  the powerful with millions.
The stadium is an integral part of my work in Night City.
It's a good question. One I've asked myself many times.
Of yours?
Call it a symbol I've grown attached to. Like the NUS flag, Night City represents a great failure.
Of principles.
Y'know, I checked whether anyone here knew you. They did mention a car... just not a Quadra.
Then forgive me. I must be mistaken.
Not very American, I know, but it's a custom my friends in Siberia taught me to love.
Oh, you are a well-traveled man.
Mhm, federal agents sniff around you still.
It's complicated. When they don't want their John Hancocks on somethin', they wire me a transfer and I set to work. Later that night, I'll watch 'em condemn my "terrorist act" on the evening news.
So they sniff around, sure, but they prefer to call direct. That's not likely to change in this admin nor the next.
We expected all to be handled professionally.
She said you did time together at La Santé, remembers you well.
I'd like to raise a little toast. To a successful day of business.
[Drink] To your health, Colonel.
Don't worry about the work, Colonel. Just your health.
Well said, Colonel, well said.
[Drink] Well said.
[Don't drink] Maybe once the work is done.
Work first, only then pleasure.
I must decline.
Your loss, little brother.
I am starting to like it here.
To your health!
Of course.
That flag's a piss-soaked pile of ash now. What I built, I built with my own two hands, for me.
Hm. Touché, Colonel.
You complement each other well... Listen, it seems we've got time to spare. There's another opportunity I'd like to discuss.
Then what more do you need from us?
An expansion, into Western Europe. What I need is a reliable partner on the ground. Two would be even better.
Comms channels, supply chains, secure transport routes, the good graces of local authorities – these things I have, the groundwork is laid.
I need an in with Le Collectif.
Aha, I see… and appreciate both the honesty and the metaphor.
Oh, is that so? Just like that?
For four... mmm, yes, contact is possible.
No "buts," no conditions?
Mhh. Close, sure, but not on the best terms from what I know.
They say to the world they would put you down. In fact, they leave you a bowl of food by the back door.
I see what you mean...
Ah, So Mi.
I come unarmed. Aymeric?
I have none. Aurore?
Fuckin' useless! Broken, fuckin' FUCK!!!
Well, seems I'm not the only one who's done their homework.
Quite right. But we almost flew here some time ago. Aymeric had other business in Night City.
My brother is obsessed with cars, he collects them. I say to him how wonderfully pretentious he is.
Interesting… And what rare gem brought you halfway 'round the world?
There are two ways to build a strong professional network. One is travel. The other – a prison term.
I thought you didn't drink.
I do not... but I understand the importance of ritual. It would be rude to reject Siberian hospitality.
By the way, Aymeric, I asked around a bit, doing my due diligence... They tell me you worked at Petrochem three years ago.
Corporations rarely let your caliber talent slip through their fingers. How did you wriggle out of the contract?
Colonel, this may be difficult to believe, but I do not remember.
You know more about me than I do.
There are many things I do not remember.
You insult me.
Hm?
I store my memories in external databanks. My databanks from that time were stolen.
Forgive me, I would like to answer, but I cannot.
Please, it's no problem.
Given when this was, I'm amazed you claim to have any memory of it at all.
It's true, my memories from that time were stolen. Those two years and what I did are lost to me.
I don't remember most of those years. My memories from that time I kept in a databank in Switzerland… until they were stolen.
You know me better than I know myself, it seems.
But I don't enjoy talking about it, and I did not expect you to know. I apologize.
I thought our collaboration was built on trust. I was sorely mistaken.
Right. On "trust."
This way.
Here we are, our stop.
This way.
So, Songbird told me a little about you. Said you two hail from Europe.
That's right.
And… did you enjoy yourselves at the Sapphire?
Police commissioner, a candidate for mayor, the Tyger Claws bookeeper – all gambling on the city's future together. Figuratively and not.
'K… Here's our stop.
Follow me, please.
Not much further now.
Cat got your tongues?
An enny for your thoughts?
We're waiting…
Is something wrong?
Cat got your tongues?
An enny for your thoughts?
We're waiting…
Is something wrong?
As agreed, you'll see the payments hit your account today.
Ahh, money and kept promises. Two of my three favorite things.
And the third?
Oh, no-no-no-no. Not yet, Kurt.
I collect many cars.
Then give my regards to Ruth as well.
Colonel... May I see your knife?
Hansen's waitin'.
Got a ways to go, still.
Everything OK?
Somethin' the matter?
Ugh, come on!
Move your ass, brother.
Aymeric…?
Hansen's waitin'.
Let's keep movin'.
Everything OK?
They're waitin' for us.
Aurore…?
We are waiting…
Shall we go?
We have little time to waste.
Aymeric…?
Shit, are you dead?
Heh, classic Aymeric. He says very little.
Dring-dring, hello…?
Aurore…?
We are waiting…
Sister, dear?
Are you daydreaming again?
Best get to it, now.
Time is money.
Can we get to work?
Coming?
Time is money.
Can we start the process?
Are you coming?
My people tell me the games went high stakes.
We won a pile of cash.
We lost all at the end.
By the end of the night, we lost our entire stack, but such is gambling.
Indeed. I was pleased our fortune turned around in the end.
Winning is not everything.
We had fun.
I do not care about money.
Does the end result matter at all? I play only for the thrill.
I care not for money, Colonel. Nor for what happens at the gambling table.
The Black Sapphire is my pride 'n' joy. I worked hard to make it the go-to destination for Night City's royalty.
Changing the subject… did you enjoy yourselves at the Sapphire? My people tell me the stakes went high.
We won a mountain of cash in the end.
We lost it all.
We, er, how do you say, uh… fucked the dog?
It was magnificent. A joy to play.
But we had fun.
Irony, Colonel.
It's not about winning.
Irony, my dear Colonel, is not your forte, no?
Life is not only about winning, Colonel. A man must learn to accept failure as well.
The Black Sapphire... My pride 'n' joy. I worked hard to make it the go-to destination for Night City's royalty.
We lost everything.
We won heaps of eddies.
We had losses but came out on top in the end.
It was unfortunate how unluckily the night ended…
It wasn't our misfortune.
One must lose for another to win.
I mean something else.
For one to win, another must lose. For one to have luck, another must have none.
Apologies. My mind was elsewhere.
We lost everything.
We made a fat stack of cash.
I thought it a night at a casino, wine and cash until both run out. But then this new piece of ass joined our table.
There were many twists, and, uh, not all of them pleasant.
Someone butted into our game.
I speak of an unwelcome guest.
I don't like surprises.
I speak of this nobody who crashed into our game and ruined my fun. You know who I mean.
I, uh… I do not like situations I do not control.
The anatomy of corruption is beautiful here.
Uh, y-yeah... Took the words right outta my mouth.
You two left richer and happier, I hope?
And this brainless cunt joined. She lost everything.
entries.maleVariant: And this brainless prick joined. He lost everything.

entries.femaleVariant: Hm. I remember the cunt. She had it comin'.
entries.maleVariant: Hm. I remember the prick. He had it comin'.

entries.femaleVariant: How unlucky you were to… double your winnings? Interesting way to look at it.
Eh, philosophy was never my strong suit.
Not even "The Art of War"?
Aha, with that exception.
Mhm. An honest mistake.
Judging by your tone, that doesn't seem to bother you at all.
Because it does not. I enjoy money, of course, but I do not allow it to control my life.
You know what they say about great minds. I think it's no surprise we find ourselves doing business together.
You... were pleased? To go bust?
Huh, well I'd expect that sentiment from your sister, but... you, Aymeric?
We are siblings, are we not?
An odd fuckin' philosophy, I must say.
You two left richer and happier, I hope?
I know the one.
Thanks to them – weiner weiner chicken dinner!
You consider doubling your money an unpleasant twist?
I remember.
Yes, this shit for brains.
An interesting choice, then, to play roulette.
Ah, I'm sorry to hear that.
No, it's OK. We will make back our losses today, and much more.
Really? Even though you lost all you brought?
Wrong. Winning is the one true measure of one's life.
Au contraire. I happen to be a master of it.
You remember the terms – one of you feeds in the access codes. The other stays with me.
You remember the terms – one of you feeds in the access codes. The other stays with me.
I will stay.
Ooh, I volunteer to stay.
I am sure my brother would like to go car shopping later. Then you and I can celebrate properly, perhaps pop a cork?
Hm-hm-hm, maybe…
Speaking of, we'll process the transfer today. As soon as they're done.
Wonderful.
An interesting knife...
By all means. It's a tradtitional Yakut hunting knife.
You see, I spent some time in the Philippines. I've had a keen eye for fine blades since.
Fascinating... Such a rare thing.
I got tickets, choom, we can go.
How you land those? Same guy as always?
Who the fuck cares? It's a belt fight, light heavyweight. Can't pass that up.
I dunno, man… I kinda got some stuff…
Refund's your problem, then. I'm goin'.
Hansen already ordered for ya.
Order's already in. We'll have those drinks to your table soon.
I'm only fucking with you, Murphy. It's a pleasure.
Goodness, Murphy, your nerves are spent. Such tense shoulders.
Tense? Haha. No, no, never better.
Ah, a relief. How silly it would be for an impressive specimen such as you to worry.
Right…
Please. Have a seat.
Care to join me?
To be honest, who cares?
Well, without money, you cannot sit at the table, it's true. But I do not need money to set that table ablaze.
As you can see, Colonel Hansen, we sometimes lack a soldier's discipline.
We could pretend to trust each other... or we could focus on business.
Well, hasn't this become awkward?
He is not, uh, hasty in action or response, as you can see.
D-dear Colonel… I-I thought we, er… commenced from the right foot, we did not?
Mmm, like in Night City, I felt, uh... suffocated by the lies, hypocrisy… the corruption. I adored it.
Hmm, it was a car owned by some rockerboy, no?
Aymeric does not partake.
A secret, Colonel.
Richer, poorer, it matters not. The game was an investment.
Aurore tells me of her friends often. Can you be more specific?
You and Myers know each other well?
Mistaken, most likely.
Kerry Eurodyne. Aurore loves his style.
Even if my sister entertains the idea, I will not.
Opportunity breeds curiosity. We are listening.
Clearly…
No, you're right.
Is that right? Seemed to me you put money on a pedestal.
Hm. Few have painted the city in such apt terms.
Ahhh, yes. Word of that sale got around.
